<title>Objects of Arrays</title>


<introduction>
<p>
    <idx><h>array</h><h>of cards</h></idx>
In the previous chapter, we defined a class to represent cards and used an array of <c>Card</c> objects to represent a deck.
In this chapter, we take additional steps toward object-oriented programming.
</p>

<p>
First we define a class to represent a deck of cards.
Then we present algorithms for shuffling and sorting decks.
Finally, we introduce <c>ArrayList</c> from the Java library and use it to represent collections of cards.
</p>
